name: Math Basics 6 Deluxe Edition Workbook
description:
Help your middle-schooler prepare for higher math. For this transitional stage in learning, Math Basics 6 builds a bridge, with features designed to summarize or define key concepts, to provide useful strategies and shortcuts, and to suggest ways to identify and avoid potential pitfalls. This 64-page workbook reviews earlier math skills, as it also helps advance into areas such as geometry and operational order. Lessons provide practice with a purpose, including word problems that address real-life applications of the concepts. Many activities offer hints and reminders, challenging problems, and interesting facts linked to the skills in the lessons. We used Principles and Standards for School Mathematics, published by the National Council for Teachers of Mathematics (NCTM), as a guide in writing this book.

Fun Features & Benefits
• Golden Scholar Club redemption code
• Parent Note inside front cover
• Activities to Share inside back cover
• 60 pages of math activities
• Tear-out pages make great individual worksheets
• Easy-reference, 4-page Answer Key
• A great value!

Skills: whole numbers; decimals; place value; rounding; estimating; powers and exponents; order of operations; mixed numbers; fractions; improper fractions; ratios; percentages; averages; probability; measurement; metric units; geometry; integers

name: Math Basics 5 Deluxe Edition Workbook
description:
Is fifth grade math getting a bit intimidating? It won't be when you can help your child become more comfortable with his or her math skills in this comprehensive fifth grade math workbook. Written and reviewed by mathematics educators, Math Basics 5 covers the most important elements in fifth grade math curriculum and gives children the tools to solve even the most difficult problems.

The workbook is aligned with the Common Core State Standards for Mathematics, a comprehensive set of learning objectives created to help students succeed in math. It is also consistent with Principles and Standards for School Mathematics, a publication by the National Council for Teachers of Mathematics (NCTM), and it is compatible with Singapore math pedagogy. The lessons are planned in learning sequence; skills introduced in one lesson build on those taught in previous lessons. It's a perfect way to introduce, review, and maintain essential math skills. Get a math edge with the School Zone Advantage!

name: Math Basics 4 Workbook
description: Your child will grow more at ease with double-digit numbers! This Math Basics 4 workbook teaches, reviews, and extends the math concepts that fourth graders need to practice the most. Lessons focus on understanding and comparing numbers through the millions, adding and subtracting multi-digit numbers, as well as working with fractions and decimals. More practice with these skills will help your child achieve greater success and confidence with math. Other suggested activities help integrate both math and language arts into everyday life. Principles and Standards for School Mathematics, published by the National Council of Teachers of Mathematics, served as a guide in writing this book.

name: Fast Ideas for Busy Teachers: Math, Grade 2
description: Mingle some math into everyday teaching! Fast Ideas for Busy Teachers: Math has hundreds of ideas that will fit into a hectic schedule and enliven second-grade students' exploration of mathematics. The book is organized by math skills, which makes it easy to find a topic when it's needed. Open-ended lessons allow adaptation of activities to meet students' needs. The lessons are perfect for substitutes, rainy-day activities, homework, and in-class assignments. The book includes tips for managing a classroom, getting organized, getting to know students, and implementing behavior management. This 80-page book also includes reproducibles and aligns with Common Core State Standards, as well as state and national standards.

name: Fast Ideas for Busy Teachers: Language Arts Resource Book
